    whatToExpect: "Metal roofing is the premium choice for Charleston homeowners who want maximum protection against our coastal weather. A standing seam metal roof typically costs $12,000-$35,000+ depending on size and material, but it delivers 50+ years of virtually maintenance-free protection \u2014 making it the best long-term value in our market.\n\nInstallation takes 3-7 days for most homes. The process involves removing the old roof, inspecting and repairing the deck, installing high-temperature synthetic underlayment, and then precisely fitting each metal panel with concealed fasteners that allow for thermal expansion. Every seam is mechanically locked or snap-locked for maximum wind resistance.\n\nThe result is a roof that laughs at hurricanes, shrugs off salt air, reflects solar heat to reduce your cooling bills by 25-40%, and looks stunning on any architectural style from historic Charleston single houses to modern Daniel Island construction.",
