    whatToExpect: "Skylights transform dark interior spaces with natural light, and they're increasingly popular in Charleston homes where the abundant sunshine can brighten kitchens, bathrooms, hallways, and living areas. A professional skylight installation typically costs $1,500-$4,000 per skylight including the unit, flashing kit, and labor.\n\nThe installation process involves cutting an opening in the roof deck (and ceiling below, if not a cathedral ceiling), framing the opening with proper headers, installing the skylight unit with a manufacturer-specific flashing kit, and ensuring watertight integration with the surrounding roofing material. For homes with attic space between the roof and ceiling, we build a light shaft (also called a light well) to direct light from the roof opening to the ceiling opening.\n\nWe install VELUX skylights exclusively \u2014 they're the industry leader in quality, energy efficiency, and leak-free performance. Options include fixed skylights, venting skylights (manual or solar-powered), and tubular skylights for smaller spaces.",
