    shortTitle: "Hail Damage",
    category: "storm",
    description: "Expert hail damage assessment and repair for Charleston-area roofs. We identify hidden hail damage, document it thoroughly for insurance, and restore your roof to pre-storm condition.",
    longDescription: "While South Carolina isn't in the traditional 'hail belt,' Charleston and the Lowcountry experience hail events more often than many homeowners realize. Severe thunderstorms can produce hail ranging from pea-sized to golf ball-sized, and even small hail can cause significant damage to asphalt shingles by knocking off the protective granule coating that shields the asphalt from UV degradation.\n\nHail damage is one of the most commonly missed types of roof damage because it's often invisible from the ground. The impact marks — circular bruises where granules have been displaced — can only be reliably identified through a hands-on roof inspection. Left unrepaired, hail damage dramatically shortens your roof's lifespan as the exposed asphalt deteriorates rapidly under South Carolina's intense UV exposure and heat.\n\nOur certified hail damage inspectors know exactly what to look for. We use industry-standard methods to identify and document hail impacts, including the chalk circle test, coin comparison for impact size, and systematic grid inspection of every roof plane. We also check soft metals (gutters, vents, flashing) and other surfaces (AC units, deck railings) for corroborating damage that strengthens your insurance claim.\n\nIf hail damage is confirmed, we provide comprehensive documentation including photos, measurements, and a detailed scope of work that your insurance adjuster can use to process your claim. We then coordinate the repair or replacement, ensuring your new roof meets or exceeds the protection of the original.",
