    longDescription: "Charleston's beautiful live oaks, towering pines, and lush tree canopy are part of what makes the Lowcountry special — but during severe storms, these same trees can become dangerous projectiles. A fallen tree on your roof is one of the most dramatic and frightening types of storm damage a homeowner can experience, and it requires immediate professional attention.\n\nFallen tree damage often involves structural compromise — broken rafters, crushed decking, and penetrations that expose your home's interior to the elements. The weight of a large tree can also stress walls, ceilings, and even the foundation. This type of damage requires careful assessment before any removal work begins to ensure the structure is safe and that removing the tree won't cause additional collapse.\n\nOur fallen tree damage response begins with a safety assessment. We work with certified arborists and structural engineers when needed to develop a safe removal plan. Once the tree is safely removed, we stabilize the structure with temporary supports and emergency tarping to prevent further damage. We then conduct a thorough assessment of all affected areas — not just the obvious impact zone, but surrounding areas where the force of impact may have caused hidden damage.\n\nThe repair process for tree damage is often more complex than other storm repairs because it may involve structural framing, decking replacement, and potentially work on interior ceilings and walls. We coordinate all aspects of the restoration, working with your insurance company to ensure the full scope of damage is covered.",
