    longDescription: "After any significant storm event in the Charleston area — whether it's a hurricane, severe thunderstorm, hail event, or tropical storm — the most important step you can take is getting a professional roof inspection. Storm damage is often invisible from the ground, and what you can't see can cost you thousands in premature roof failure and water damage down the road.\n\nRestoration Roofing offers free, no-obligation post-storm roof inspections throughout the greater Charleston area. Our certified inspectors conduct a systematic, multi-point evaluation of your entire roof system — not just a quick glance from the ground. We inspect every component: shingles or roofing material, flashing at all transitions, ridge and hip caps, pipe boots and vent covers, gutters and downspouts, fascia and soffit, and the attic space for signs of water intrusion.\n\nWe use a combination of hands-on inspection and drone technology to evaluate every square foot of your roof, including areas that are difficult or dangerous to access on foot. Our drone inspections provide high-resolution imagery that can reveal damage patterns invisible to the naked eye.\n\nAfter the inspection, we provide you with a detailed written report including photos of any damage found, an assessment of severity, and our recommended course of action. If damage is found that warrants an insurance claim, we'll walk you through the process and provide all the documentation your insurance company needs.\n\nEven if no damage is found, you'll have peace of mind knowing your roof weathered the storm successfully — and you'll have a baseline inspection report that can be valuable for future reference.",
